# Description:
hda2csg is a function that maps a couple (hda, pn), where hda is the maxcell representation of the higher-dimensional automaton (HDA) for the Petri-net (PN) pn, to the corresponding concurrent step graph (CSG) of the HDA.

## Dependencies:
Require the modules spot (https://spot.lre.epita.fr/index.html), argparse, dataclasses, subprocess, glob, typing and pathlib.
Also requires the executables pn2HDA and pn2MAXHDA from the parent project.

## Usage:
Run "python3.12 hda2csg.py -p--path YOUR/PATH/TO/DIR example/pn_file.pnml example/io_file.txt", where "YOUR/PATH/TO/DIR" replaced by your path to the directory containing the executables pn2HDA and pn2MAXHDA, to output the controler in Hanoi Omega-Automata format(https://spot.lre.epita.fr/hoa.html).

If the executables are in a folder in the parent directory pn2hda, the "-p--path YOUR/PATH/TO/DIR" is optional: "python3.12 hda2csg.py example/pn_file.pnml example/io_file.txt".

The function build_csg_from_files() builds the controller from the specification files for the hda, the Petri net and the input/output.

### Example:
python3.12 hda2csg.py ../pnml_files/basic/abx_squared.pnml example/io_example.txt

### io file format
The file specifying the inputs and outputs of the Petri net should be in the following form (strictly between the % symbols):
%
Inputs: (input1,input2,...,inputn)
Outputs: (output1,output2,...,outputm)
<Transitions>
(number_transition,"id_transition"): (input_formula;output_formula)
...
</Transitions>
<Place-Output>
number_place:(output_formula)
...
</Place-Output>
%
where
- number_transition is the number of the transition by appearance in the pnml file (starting at 0)
- number_place is the number of the place by appearance in the pnml file (starting at 0)
- name_transition is in the <id> field of the transition in the pnml file
- formulas are propositions or negation of propositions (by adding "!" before the proposition) separated by conjunctive operators ("&").